00:14:35.707 --> 00:14:37.290
ALICE MARIE JOHNSON:
The fact is there

00:14:37.290 --> 00:14:41.160
is no parole in the
federal system--

00:14:41.160 --> 00:14:46.890
for most of us, for me,
clemency has been our only hope.

00:14:46.890 --> 00:14:51.240
So to not push for clemency
is to take away their hope.

00:14:51.240 --> 00:14:54.990
Because we have exhausted
all of the means.

00:14:54.990 --> 00:14:56.590
I have not been sitting still.

00:14:56.590 --> 00:14:59.940
I have filed motion after
motion in the court.

00:14:59.940 --> 00:15:04.140
But clemency, in itself, is an
act of mercy and forgiveness.

00:15:04.140 --> 00:15:06.150
And when you see a
person like myself

00:15:06.150 --> 00:15:10.020
who has did a complete
turn around in their life,

00:15:10.020 --> 00:15:11.040
who has gotten--

00:15:11.040 --> 00:15:12.450
I've gotten so much support.

00:15:12.450 --> 00:15:14.460
My family fought so hard.

00:15:14.460 --> 00:15:17.400
The Clemency Project was
