Thank you for
allowing me to speak.

01:02:53.904 --> 01:02:56.320
ANA KASPARIAN: So we were just
having a great conversation

01:02:56.320 --> 01:03:02.500
with your daughter about some
of the obstacles to establishing

01:03:02.500 --> 01:03:04.290
a bond between the two of you.

01:03:04.290 --> 01:03:06.975
And we heard her side of
the story, her perspective.

01:03:06.975 --> 01:03:08.350
And I was hoping
that we can also

01:03:08.350 --> 01:03:11.240
hear your perspective as well.

01:03:11.240 --> 01:03:17.260
SANTRA RUCKER: OK, well, it's
like the dynamics of being

01:03:17.260 --> 01:03:20.950
incarcerated is really sensitive
when it comes to a mother

01:03:20.950 --> 01:03:25.420
and daughter
relationship, because you

01:03:25.420 --> 01:03:29.440
don't want your child to have
any type of resentment or anger

01:03:29.440 --> 01:03:33.370
because she feels
abandoned or whatever

01:03:33.370 --> 01:03:35.860
situation is due to
my circumstances that

01:03:35.860 --> 01:03:37.900
led me to come to prison.

01:03:37.900 --> 01:03:41.740
You know, these are
the things that I hope.

01:03:41.740 --> 01:03:47.050
But people might feel that
it is wrong for me to say,

01:03:47.050 --> 01:03:52.240
like I'm not really
remorseful for the things that

01:03:52.240 --> 01:03:53.930
led me to come to prison.

01:03:53.930 --> 01:03:57.490
In fact, I think that
the greater gravity was

01:03:57.490 --> 01:04:00.820
my choice and my poor choices.

01:04:00.820 --> 01:04:04.270
At the time, I didn't think
that those choices would affect

01:04:04.270 --> 01:04:09.010
my children or my family,
because I was doing the things

01:04:09.010 --> 01:04:11.930
that I love to do at the time.

01:04:11.930 --> 01:04:15.220
So at the same time, I
don't want to beat myself up

01:04:15.220 --> 01:04:18.850
for my past to make
my relationship better

01:04:18.850 --> 01:04:23.130
with my daughter because
I can't change the past.

01:04:23.130 --> 01:04:26.920
So what I'm doing is I'm trying
to benefit from the past,

01:04:26.920 --> 01:04:28.210
and move on.

01:04:28.210 --> 01:04:31.330
But in my own belief,
I believe that karma

01:04:31.330 --> 01:04:35.230
plays a big part in the
conditions of my imprisonment,

01:04:35.230 --> 01:04:37.950
because that's my
personal belief.

01:04:37.950 --> 01:04:41.430
But at the same time, I
believe that whatever you are,

01:04:41.430 --> 01:04:43.340
and whatever you are
not, you earned it

01:04:43.340 --> 01:04:46.570
whether it's good or
bad and whatever you are

01:04:46.570 --> 01:04:47.800
or whatever you are not--

01:04:47.800 --> 01:04:50.330
SPEAKER 1: This call is
from a federal prison.

01:04:50.330 --> 01:04:52.120
SANTRA RUCKER: And
right now I feel like I

01:04:52.120 --> 01:04:54.430
have changed dramatically.

01:04:54.430 --> 01:04:57.700
And I have [INAUDIBLE] raised
my level of consciousness

01:04:57.700 --> 01:05:02.320
to a higher vibration so that
I can be able to be active with

01:05:02.320 --> 01:05:06.310
my daughter, to show love for
my daughter, to do the things--

01:05:06.310 --> 01:05:08.530
not trying to make
up for my past,

01:05:08.530 --> 01:05:10.600
but the things that
a mother would do.

01:05:10.600 --> 01:05:14.500
I try to do these things over
the phone, through the emails,

01:05:14.500 --> 01:05:17.890
through visitation, sending
things to my daughter

01:05:17.890 --> 01:05:20.350
to show her that I
love her and that I

01:05:20.350 --> 01:05:21.960
am sorry to not be there.

01:05:21.960 --> 01:05:25.662
So in my absence, I do
things from my heart.

01:05:25.662 --> 01:05:29.172
[SOBBING]

01:05:29.172 --> 01:05:30.880
ANA KASPARIAN: Kendia
talked a little bit

01:05:30.880 --> 01:05:35.710
about what it was like to
have physical contact with you

01:05:35.710 --> 01:05:37.420
for the first time.

01:05:37.420 --> 01:05:42.360
I'm curious to hear what
that felt like for you.

01:05:42.360 --> 01:05:45.820
SANTRA RUCKER: It
felt kind of awkward.

01:05:45.820 --> 01:05:50.930
Because you don't
know what to say.

01:05:50.930 --> 01:05:53.330
Like I wanted to
be a mother, but I

01:05:53.330 --> 01:05:58.040
didn't want to act too
overprotective, because

01:05:58.040 --> 01:06:01.120
of my absence,
due to my absence.

01:06:01.120 --> 01:06:04.450
But I wanted to show her that,
yeah, true, I am your mother.

01:06:04.450 --> 01:06:07.000
And I want you to
be open with me.

01:06:07.000 --> 01:06:09.160
I want you to
understand me, and I

01:06:09.160 --> 01:06:12.490
want you to learn who I
am through visitation,

01:06:12.490 --> 01:06:16.360
because we only would
talk over the phone.

01:06:16.360 --> 01:06:21.970
And it was kind of a bonding
time, where I looked at her

01:06:21.970 --> 01:06:24.540
and she looked at me.

01:06:24.540 --> 01:06:27.180
But at the same time, I
didn't know what to say.

01:06:27.180 --> 01:06:30.910
I didn't know if I
should touch her.

01:06:30.910 --> 01:06:35.650
I didn't know if
she would reject me.

01:06:35.650 --> 01:06:40.365
So I watch how other
people in the visitation

01:06:40.365 --> 01:06:43.090
interacted with their children.

01:06:43.090 --> 01:06:44.800
So that I can learn
that, OK, this

01:06:44.800 --> 01:06:46.620
is all right to hold her hand.

01:06:46.620 --> 01:06:50.830
This is all right to do this,
or this is all right to do that.

01:06:50.830 --> 01:06:51.910
But it was pretty--

01:06:51.910 --> 01:06:55.420
it was more emotional
for me when I came back.

01:06:55.420 --> 01:06:59.600
Because I was, like, I wish
I would have said this.

01:06:59.600 --> 01:07:01.600
I wish I would have said that.

01:07:01.600 --> 01:07:04.810
And when she came to
visit me, my other family

01:07:04.810 --> 01:07:06.690
was there-- my
sisters, my nephews,

01:07:06.690 --> 01:07:09.650
so I couldn't be
as personal as I

01:07:09.650 --> 01:07:12.730
wanted to be and say the
things that I really wanted to.

01:07:12.730 --> 01:07:14.130
Because it was so long.

01:07:14.130 --> 01:07:16.345
It had been 10
years before I had

01:07:16.345 --> 01:07:19.690
seen my family and my daughter.

01:07:19.690 --> 01:07:22.080
So it was just really hard.

01:07:22.080 --> 01:07:27.250
It's even harder when you have
to come back from visitation.

01:07:27.250 --> 01:07:30.500
You know and to be around total
strangers that you don't love,

01:07:30.500 --> 01:07:32.000
and that you don't know.

01:07:32.000 --> 01:07:34.000
You know?

01:07:34.000 --> 01:07:35.200
So, I'm sorry.

01:07:35.200 --> 01:07:35.867
Can you hear me?

01:07:35.867 --> 01:07:37.324
ANA KASPARIAN: Yes,
I can hear you.

01:07:37.324 --> 01:07:39.100
Thank you so much for
sharing your story.

01:07:39.100 --> 01:07:40.240
It's very moving.

01:07:40.240 --> 01:07:42.490
And everyone-- there
are several members

01:07:42.490 --> 01:07:45.760
of the audience that are in
tears right now over what

01:07:45.760 --> 01:07:47.410
you're saying.

01:07:47.410 --> 01:07:51.050
So Kendia has done incredible
things with her life.

01:07:51.050 --> 01:07:53.990
She is a sophomore at the
University of Virginia.

01:07:53.990 --> 01:07:56.710
She's studying majors
that I can't even

01:07:56.710 --> 01:07:57.940
wrap my brain around.

01:07:57.940 --> 01:08:00.620
She's an incredible young woman.

01:08:00.620 --> 01:08:04.216
So what are your
feelings about that?

01:08:04.216 --> 01:08:06.270
SANTRA RUCKER: I'm very proud.

01:08:06.270 --> 01:08:10.810
And I feel, sometimes I wonder
if my absence made her life

01:08:10.810 --> 01:08:12.580
better.

01:08:12.580 --> 01:08:17.450
Because she was raised by
the same parents as me.

01:08:17.450 --> 01:08:19.580
That's my mom and dad.

01:08:19.580 --> 01:08:23.830
So I knew she would be a
good person, a loving person.

01:08:23.830 --> 01:08:26.439
You know, but I'm glad.

01:08:26.439 --> 01:08:29.439
I feel like she's the
better side of me.

01:08:29.439 --> 01:08:30.120
You know?

01:08:30.120 --> 01:08:32.700
Like, I feel like
I couldn't make it.

01:08:32.700 --> 01:08:33.609
And I didn't make it.

01:08:33.609 --> 01:08:37.229
And I wasn't successful
like I wanted to be.

01:08:37.229 --> 01:08:39.580
So I figure that
with her doing it,

01:08:39.580 --> 01:08:42.580
it makes me feel proud
because she is me.

01:08:42.580 --> 01:08:44.170
She's a part of me.

01:08:44.170 --> 01:08:47.560
And I knew that she
would do great things.

01:08:47.560 --> 01:08:51.620
And I just always knew that she
had she has great potential.

01:08:51.620 --> 01:08:53.770
So I wasn't shocked
that she would

01:08:53.770 --> 01:08:57.460
be as productive and intelligent
as she is in everything

01:08:57.460 --> 01:08:59.479
that she's displaying.

01:08:59.479 --> 01:09:00.210
You know?

01:09:00.210 --> 01:09:04.439
So I knew that she would
be all right, you know?

01:09:04.439 --> 01:09:08.710
But I often wonder, if
I was home to raise her,

01:09:08.710 --> 01:09:12.700
would she have taken that route?

01:09:12.700 --> 01:09:17.910
Maybe my poor choices would have
infected her and affected her.

01:09:17.910 --> 01:09:21.750
You know, so I was kind of
glad to be absent in a way

01:09:21.750 --> 01:09:24.107
so that she could have
the perfect life that I

01:09:24.107 --> 01:09:25.061
didn't have.

01:09:27.340 --> 01:09:28.840
ANA KASPARIAN:
Kendia shared with us

01:09:28.840 --> 01:09:32.420
that you, fortunately,
finally, have a release date.

01:09:32.420 --> 01:09:37.120
So I'm curious what
you maybe fantasize

01:09:37.120 --> 01:09:39.819
about doing with your family,
doing with Kendia when

01:09:39.819 --> 01:09:42.670
you are released.

01:09:42.670 --> 01:09:44.800
SANTRA RUCKER:
Well, a lot of times

01:09:44.800 --> 01:09:46.960
I see, I listen to a lot
of prisoners that leave.

01:09:46.960 --> 01:09:48.590
They make big plans.

01:09:48.590 --> 01:09:51.040
And that folder seems
to be somewhere lost

01:09:51.040 --> 01:09:53.410
in the attic when they get home.

01:09:53.410 --> 01:09:55.930
But I know one of
the biggest problems

01:09:55.930 --> 01:09:59.750
that my family faces
is financial problems.

01:09:59.750 --> 01:10:02.710
So I've been in
here studying how

01:10:02.710 --> 01:10:05.440
to learn the different
grants that's available

01:10:05.440 --> 01:10:08.410
when I get out, the different
loans that they have

01:10:08.410 --> 01:10:13.120
for convicted felons, and try
to use those things to open up

01:10:13.120 --> 01:10:16.690
a restaurant where my
family can benefit from.

01:10:16.690 --> 01:10:20.871
And I think finances is of
great importance for everybody

01:10:20.871 --> 01:10:21.370
in life.

01:10:21.370 --> 01:10:24.790
Because without money, you
can't really do anything.

01:10:24.790 --> 01:10:27.790
And I believe that we can
come together as a family

01:10:27.790 --> 01:10:32.050
and be productive and have
fun and go places and travel.

01:10:32.050 --> 01:10:35.230
And do the things, not
to make up for lost time,

01:10:35.230 --> 01:10:38.120
but for the now.

01:10:38.120 --> 01:10:40.640
And so I hope to have a
restaurant when I get out.

01:10:40.640 --> 01:10:42.040
I took culinary art.

01:10:42.040 --> 01:10:46.210
And I taught Kendia how to
bake over this telephone.

01:10:46.210 --> 01:10:49.430
So I'm hoping that I can do
that, not just for myself,

01:10:49.430 --> 01:10:51.430
but for my family.

01:10:51.430 --> 01:10:53.680
That's one of the main things.

01:10:53.680 --> 01:10:57.860
And I just want to be a
mother to my daughter.

01:10:57.860 --> 01:11:01.545
And those things I have tried
to do from prison, which

01:11:01.545 --> 01:11:04.500
I have great limitations here.

01:11:04.500 --> 01:11:07.630
But I believe when I get
home, it could be better.

01:11:07.630 --> 01:11:10.540
But it depends on my daughter.

01:11:10.540 --> 01:11:13.840
Because if my daughter
feels that I abandoned

01:11:13.840 --> 01:11:16.990
her or she feels any
resentment, or she feels

01:11:16.990 --> 01:11:20.560
any anger towards my
absence, then it's

01:11:20.560 --> 01:11:22.960
going to be quite difficult
for me to do the things

01:11:22.960 --> 01:11:26.990
that I would love to do and
have the great desire to do.

01:11:26.990 --> 01:11:31.600
But it has to be a
mutual agreement.

01:11:31.600 --> 01:11:34.630
And I just hope to be the
most successful person

01:11:34.630 --> 01:11:35.890
that I can be.

01:11:35.890 --> 01:11:40.570
I want to be the person
that I was in 1999 before I

01:11:40.570 --> 01:11:42.160
came to prison.

01:11:42.160 --> 01:11:43.540
So I have high goals.

01:11:43.540 --> 01:11:44.710
I have high standards.

01:11:44.710 --> 01:11:46.280
I have high principles.

01:11:46.280 --> 01:11:49.940
And I believe, that with
God being in my life,

01:11:49.940 --> 01:11:53.680
that these things are
manifesting before I even

01:11:53.680 --> 01:11:55.960
come home, you know.

01:11:55.960 --> 01:11:58.210
So I'm not waiting
for the manifestation

01:11:58.210 --> 01:12:01.170
to take place when
I walk out the door.

01:12:01.170 --> 01:12:02.695
I'm preparing it now.

01:12:02.695 --> 01:12:04.630
Through my provision,
through my prayers,

01:12:04.630 --> 01:12:08.080
and through what I know,
which is my belief.

01:12:08.080 --> 01:12:12.410
But I believe that we were
all one, and we'll be one.

01:12:12.410 --> 01:12:15.520
It's kind of hard to be
one from prison, because

01:12:15.520 --> 01:12:18.460
of the barricades that we face.

01:12:18.460 --> 01:12:22.000
But hopefully, I hope that,
through my mom and dad,

01:12:22.000 --> 01:12:23.560
that the love that
they instilled

01:12:23.560 --> 01:12:26.020
in me, the human
compassion that they

01:12:26.020 --> 01:12:27.900
instilled in me,
that they instilled

01:12:27.900 --> 01:12:29.700
those things into Kendia.

01:12:29.700 --> 01:12:34.710
So when I get home, everything
will be as if I never left.

01:12:34.710 --> 01:12:36.580
And that's how I would like it.

01:12:36.580 --> 01:12:41.540
That's how I want it to
be when I touch home.

01:12:41.540 --> 01:12:42.330
I'm sorry.

01:12:42.330 --> 01:12:43.550
I get a little emotional.

01:12:43.550 --> 01:12:44.675
ANA KASPARIAN: No, it's OK.

01:12:44.675 --> 01:12:48.730
SANTRA RUCKER: But you know,
but you know, I'm sorry?

01:12:48.730 --> 01:12:50.880
ANA KASPARIAN: No, go ahead.

01:12:50.880 --> 01:12:53.310
SANTRA RUCKER: But you know,
I understand where I am.

01:12:53.310 --> 01:12:55.760
I understand the
circumstances of my life.

01:12:55.760 --> 01:12:58.960
And the events that took
shape to get me here,

01:12:58.960 --> 01:13:01.510
and the people who
I gravitated to.

01:13:01.510 --> 01:13:06.154
But during that era of the '80s,
that was like the 'in' thing--

01:13:06.154 --> 01:13:08.070
SPEAKER 1: This call is
from a federal prison.

01:13:08.070 --> 01:13:10.400
SANTRA RUCKER: --what was
happening at the time.

01:13:10.400 --> 01:13:10.750
ANA KASPARIAN: Miss--

01:13:10.750 --> 01:13:12.541
SANTRA RUCKER: And the
decision that I made

01:13:12.541 --> 01:13:15.080
were what I thought
were good decisions.

01:13:15.080 --> 01:13:19.560
It was just normal and typical
for people my age in that area.

01:13:19.560 --> 01:13:22.200
ANA KASPARIAN: Miss Santra
Rucker, sorry to interrupt you.

01:13:22.200 --> 01:13:24.710
I just want to let you know
that we might lose you soon.

01:13:24.710 --> 01:13:27.590
And if we do, I just want
to thank you for your time.

01:13:27.590 --> 01:13:31.240
And thank you for speaking
with us and sharing your story.

01:13:31.240 --> 01:13:33.410
SANTRA RUCKER: No, and I
thank you for allowing me.

01:13:33.410 --> 01:13:36.110
I thank you for having
human compassion,

01:13:36.110 --> 01:13:38.120
to be able to be a
sensitive audience.

01:13:38.120 --> 01:13:41.050
That-- just take this
as a shift of awareness

01:13:41.050 --> 01:13:42.710
and know that, I
just know everything

01:13:42.710 --> 01:13:45.410
is going to be all right just
from speaking to you all.

01:13:45.410 --> 01:13:47.520
And I think you all can
make a big difference.

01:13:47.520 --> 01:13:51.860
And I thank you
again, I really do.

01:13:51.860 --> 01:13:53.990
Because you have an
influential power

01:13:53.990 --> 01:13:55.760
that can change your life.

01:13:55.760 --> 01:13:58.800
And just from the audience
being there today,

01:13:58.800 --> 01:14:04.130
this shows that everybody's
destiny and fate can change.

01:14:04.130 --> 01:14:06.740
And you could be really
influential and encouraging

01:14:06.740 --> 01:14:08.780
to prisoners as well.

01:14:08.780 --> 01:14:11.290
Because it's difficult.
It's very difficult.

01:14:11.290 --> 01:14:14.840
It's difficult for our children
and for us as prisoners.

01:14:14.840 --> 01:14:17.380
But I thank you as well.

01:14:17.380 --> 01:14:18.972
Start crying.

01:14:18.972 --> 01:14:20.930
ANA KASPARIAN: You have
no reason to apologize.

01:14:20.930 --> 01:14:23.790
Please take care of yourself,
and thank you again.

01:14:23.790 --> 01:14:25.200
SANTRA RUCKER: OK, thank you.

