01:15:52.530 --> 01:15:55.170
advocate for various
social justice

01:15:55.170 --> 01:15:57.780
issues such as criminal
justice reform, human sex

01:15:57.780 --> 01:15:59.480
trafficking, and foster care.

01:15:59.480 --> 01:16:01.230
And I sit on various
boards and committees

01:16:01.230 --> 01:16:03.864
throughout the state that
address these issues.

01:16:03.864 --> 01:16:05.280
MICHELLE DIAZ: Hi,
good afternoon.

01:16:05.280 --> 01:16:06.390
My name is Michelle Diaz.

01:16:06.390 --> 01:16:08.730
I'm an advisor
for the task force

01:16:08.730 --> 01:16:10.530
in ending girls'
incarceration in New York

01:16:10.530 --> 01:16:12.930
City for Vera Institute.

01:16:12.930 --> 01:16:14.850
SARAH ZARBA: Hi,
my name is Sarah.

01:16:14.850 --> 01:16:16.770
I'm actually also part
of that task force

01:16:16.770 --> 01:16:19.210
and I'm also working at the
Vera Institute of Justice

01:16:19.210 --> 01:16:21.045
in New York City.

01:16:21.045 --> 01:16:22.920
MALIKA SAADA SAAR: So
beginning with Charity,

01:16:22.920 --> 01:16:25.830
if you could each
talk about how you

01:16:25.830 --> 01:16:28.650
were placed into
the juvenile justice

01:16:28.650 --> 01:16:30.354
system and your
experiences there.

01:16:30.354 --> 01:16:31.770
CHARITY CHANDLER-COLE:
Absolutely.

01:16:31.770 --> 01:16:36.630
So at the age of 10, my mother
was going through a divorce,

01:16:36.630 --> 01:16:38.520
and she got breast
cancer at the same time.

01:16:38.520 --> 01:16:40.980
And she pretty much
afterwards went

01:16:40.980 --> 01:16:43.360
through a state of depression,
stress, and anxiety.

01:16:43.360 --> 01:16:47.400
And she basically just gave up
on the six children she had,

01:16:47.400 --> 01:16:49.380
and we kind of had to
fend for ourselves.

01:16:49.380 --> 01:16:51.780
My older sister entered
the juvenile justice

01:16:51.780 --> 01:16:53.800
and foster care system
at the age of 12.

01:16:53.800 --> 01:16:56.352
So when I was 14, I
was the big sister.

01:16:56.352 --> 01:16:57.060
I was the mother.

01:16:57.060 --> 01:17:00.630
And I did everything I could
to provide for my four younger

01:17:00.630 --> 01:17:03.890
siblings while we
were on welfare.

01:17:03.890 --> 01:17:08.460
At the age of 16, I got caught
stealing underwear from Ross.

01:17:08.460 --> 01:17:09.870
Nothing cute, it was Hanes.

01:17:09.870 --> 01:17:13.230
You know, from a
sibling, so it was simply

01:17:13.230 --> 01:17:15.900
out of a pure desire
of need for my family.

01:17:15.900 --> 01:17:19.140
And the police called
my mother to pick me up,

01:17:19.140 --> 01:17:20.910
and she said, take her to jail.

01:17:20.910 --> 01:17:21.570
And they did.

01:17:21.570 --> 01:17:24.750
And my mom at the time used the
foster care system and juvenile

01:17:24.750 --> 01:17:28.800
justice system to kind of one
by one get rid of the children

01:17:28.800 --> 01:17:32.040
that she no longer desired
to have at the time.

01:17:32.040 --> 01:17:33.790
It wasn't because she
just didn't love us,

01:17:33.790 --> 01:17:35.581
she just didn't know
how to take care of us

01:17:35.581 --> 01:17:37.650
any longer after
what she experienced.

01:17:40.710 --> 01:17:42.990
After there, I spent the
next two years in and out

01:17:42.990 --> 01:17:45.480
of juvenile hall
and foster care.

01:17:45.480 --> 01:17:47.850
No one at any point
asked my mother

01:17:47.850 --> 01:17:49.850
why do you want your
child to go to jail?

01:17:49.850 --> 01:17:51.870
You know, why is she
stealing underwear?

01:17:51.870 --> 01:17:53.850
What situation is
happening in your family

01:17:53.850 --> 01:17:57.630
to cause your daughter
to steal underwear?

01:17:57.630 --> 01:18:00.450
Here are some alternatives
to incarceration.

01:18:00.450 --> 01:18:03.422
I was just-- they said,
OK, they hung up the phone.

01:18:03.422 --> 01:18:05.880
They handcuffed me, put me in
the back of their patrol car,

01:18:05.880 --> 01:18:08.800
booked me, and took
me to juvenile hall.

01:18:08.800 --> 01:18:13.530
I, at that very moment, realized
that my life had zero value,

01:18:13.530 --> 01:18:16.470
and that I could easily
be discarded and put away.

01:18:16.470 --> 01:18:18.630
My experience in
the juvenile justice

01:18:18.630 --> 01:18:21.660
system and the foster
care system were horrid.

01:18:21.660 --> 01:18:23.190
And I experienced
and was exposed

01:18:23.190 --> 01:18:26.250
to things I probably would
have never experienced

01:18:26.250 --> 01:18:29.160
living in the streets in a
gang-infested and drug-infested

01:18:29.160 --> 01:18:30.690
neighborhood.

01:18:30.690 --> 01:18:33.000
Any ounce of self-esteem
and confidence

01:18:33.000 --> 01:18:36.750
I have went out the window,
and I was constantly degraded.

01:18:36.750 --> 01:18:40.590
I felt enslaved, and I
was psychologically abused

01:18:40.590 --> 01:18:43.300
and sexually exploited
while in the system.

01:18:43.300 --> 01:18:45.450
And because of
what I experienced

01:18:45.450 --> 01:18:49.080
and because of the feeling of
abandoning the four siblings

01:18:49.080 --> 01:18:51.720
that needed me-- who was going
to feed them and take care

01:18:51.720 --> 01:18:55.280
of them, who's going to walk
them to school the next day--

01:18:55.280 --> 01:18:58.710
just feeling completely
just abandoned, alone,

01:18:58.710 --> 01:19:01.860
and worthless, I left
the system determined

01:19:01.860 --> 01:19:04.770
that I was going to work my
ass off for the rest of my life

01:19:04.770 --> 01:19:05.590
to help change it.

01:19:05.590 --> 01:19:13.820
[APPLAUSE]

01:19:13.820 --> 01:19:16.250
MICHELLE DIAZ: Well, everything
started when I was 13.

01:19:16.250 --> 01:19:18.680
I'm only 20.

01:19:18.680 --> 01:19:20.600
I came here.

01:19:20.600 --> 01:19:23.030
I did not speak English
at all, and my mother

01:19:23.030 --> 01:19:25.730
was working seven days a week.

01:19:25.730 --> 01:19:29.640
And the only person that I
knew was my mother, and then

01:19:29.640 --> 01:19:30.440
nobody else.

01:19:30.440 --> 01:19:36.320
When I went to school, my
school class was only Spanish,

01:19:36.320 --> 01:19:39.710
so I didn't really
learn English at all.

01:19:39.710 --> 01:19:45.530
And when I was going
to school, I was shy.

01:19:45.530 --> 01:19:47.450
I didn't talk to the other kids.

01:19:47.450 --> 01:19:50.450
And then one time, I just
went to McDonald's, and I

01:19:50.450 --> 01:19:51.530
met this guy.

01:19:51.530 --> 01:19:54.230
And you know, he was
much older than me--

01:19:54.230 --> 01:19:55.910
keeping in mind
that I was only 13--

01:19:55.910 --> 01:19:58.220
and he talked to me.

01:19:58.220 --> 01:20:01.370
And you know, like I
said, my mother never

01:20:01.370 --> 01:20:02.990
had the time to be with me.

01:20:02.990 --> 01:20:07.560
And the reason why I
moved to United States,

01:20:07.560 --> 01:20:10.580
it was because I wanted to
have that mother and daughter

01:20:10.580 --> 01:20:15.240
relationship, because my mother
all the time, she was working.

01:20:15.240 --> 01:20:19.910
And then this guy
who treat me "right,"

01:20:19.910 --> 01:20:21.770
quote unquote, who
pay attention to me,

01:20:21.770 --> 01:20:24.800
make me being the
idea of being in love.

01:20:24.800 --> 01:20:27.650
And one time, like
I was going crazy--

01:20:27.650 --> 01:20:30.600
the only person that I
really pay attention to--

01:20:30.600 --> 01:20:32.320
and one time we just
went to the mall

01:20:32.320 --> 01:20:36.620
and he stole a tee shirt
from JC Penney, 25 bucks.

01:20:36.620 --> 01:20:38.730
And we got caught.

01:20:38.730 --> 01:20:41.060
And he was like, oh,
Michelle, take the charge.

01:20:41.060 --> 01:20:41.750
Take the charge.

01:20:41.750 --> 01:20:43.374
They're not going to
do nothing to you.

01:20:43.374 --> 01:20:44.180
You're under age.

01:20:44.180 --> 01:20:47.720
And I was like, no, it's not
my fault. And he was like,

01:20:47.720 --> 01:20:49.130
oh, he started arguing with me.

01:20:49.130 --> 01:20:51.230
And of course, you don't want
to be mad with the person--

01:20:51.230 --> 01:20:53.810
you don't want the person to
be mad at you, the only person

01:20:53.810 --> 01:20:55.310
who's paying attention to you.

01:20:55.310 --> 01:20:57.260
So I said, yeah,
I take the charge.

01:20:57.260 --> 01:20:59.990
And then I will spend
the night at the prison.

01:20:59.990 --> 01:21:01.772
And then my mother
came and took me.

01:21:01.772 --> 01:21:02.980
And the next day, I run away.

01:21:02.980 --> 01:21:04.370
I went back to him.

01:21:04.370 --> 01:21:06.740
And this was like
a family court.

01:21:06.740 --> 01:21:10.710
And my lawyer was like, oh,
Michelle, just take the charge.

01:21:10.710 --> 01:21:12.620
It's going to be 18
months of probation.

01:21:12.620 --> 01:21:15.822
And of course, I did
not know nothing.

01:21:15.822 --> 01:21:16.780
I didn't speak English.

01:21:16.780 --> 01:21:19.550
My lawyer was only
speak English.

01:21:19.550 --> 01:21:21.230
So it was really, really hard.

01:21:21.230 --> 01:21:23.960
The interpreter was there
only for like two minutes.

01:21:23.960 --> 01:21:26.587
And I was like,
yeah, sure, whatever.

01:21:26.587 --> 01:21:28.045
And then one thing
lead to another.

01:21:28.045 --> 01:21:29.720
I started missing school.

01:21:29.720 --> 01:21:31.850
I got pregnant at 15.

01:21:31.850 --> 01:21:35.640
I was in seventh grade, and
like all these things crash.

01:21:35.640 --> 01:21:38.120
I run away.

01:21:38.120 --> 01:21:40.880
Got a warrant and a
violation of probation.

01:21:40.880 --> 01:21:43.460
I went back because I always
wanted to do the right thing.

01:21:43.460 --> 01:21:44.780
I always wanted to be somebody.

01:21:44.780 --> 01:21:47.690
But never nobody
asked me why I was

01:21:47.690 --> 01:21:50.360
doing what I was doing, what I
wanted to be, where am I going,

01:21:50.360 --> 01:21:52.040
what is my future, right?

01:21:52.040 --> 01:21:54.740
In the end, I went back.

01:21:54.740 --> 01:21:58.610
I try, I try to do things right.

01:21:58.610 --> 01:22:00.440
But there was no support at all.

01:22:00.440 --> 01:22:03.050
And I was a teenage mom.

01:22:03.050 --> 01:22:07.460
And I dropped out of middle
school, never graduated.

01:22:07.460 --> 01:22:11.180
And I couldn't
take it any longer.

01:22:11.180 --> 01:22:14.870
And my probation officer
violated me again.

01:22:14.870 --> 01:22:16.220
I ran away.

01:22:16.220 --> 01:22:18.710
Then the judge said
that I was a runner,

01:22:18.710 --> 01:22:22.820
and he put me in a secure
facility in New York.

01:22:22.820 --> 01:22:26.600
And I spent like, about eight,
six to eight months in there.

01:22:26.600 --> 01:22:29.750
And after that I went
to a group home close

01:22:29.750 --> 01:22:32.090
to home, a secure facility.

01:22:32.090 --> 01:22:37.070
And it was when I started
speaking English was when

01:22:37.070 --> 01:22:39.230
I was in this secure facility.

01:22:39.230 --> 01:22:41.075
Because nobody spoke
Spanish over there.

01:22:41.075 --> 01:22:43.790
But I could put together
the images, what I see,

01:22:43.790 --> 01:22:44.870
what I hear.

01:22:44.870 --> 01:22:45.950
And it was amazing.

01:22:45.950 --> 01:22:48.691
But the first time I was
there, I couldn't eat.

01:22:48.691 --> 01:22:49.190
Why?

01:22:49.190 --> 01:22:51.350
Because I didn't like the food.

01:22:51.350 --> 01:22:53.360
I just, I couldn't take it.

01:22:53.360 --> 01:22:58.620
Nobody wanted how I lost 10, 20
pounds in a month over there.

01:22:58.620 --> 01:23:04.820
And when I got out, I spent
two months in a group home.

01:23:04.820 --> 01:23:06.650
But I was always scared.

01:23:06.650 --> 01:23:09.410
People talk about Rikers
Island, the secure facility,

01:23:09.410 --> 01:23:11.030
and how bad it is.

01:23:11.030 --> 01:23:13.370
And I was like, damn, I
don't want to go there.

01:23:13.370 --> 01:23:15.060
I was so afraid,
because at that time,

01:23:15.060 --> 01:23:16.910
I didn't have papers at all.

01:23:16.910 --> 01:23:19.880
And then I was like,
if I do something,

01:23:19.880 --> 01:23:21.000
and there was this girl.

01:23:21.000 --> 01:23:22.580
She was 15 and
tried to fight me.

01:23:22.580 --> 01:23:24.220
And I was like, I
can't get into her.

01:23:24.220 --> 01:23:25.982
Because what is next?

01:23:25.982 --> 01:23:27.940
Next thing you know, I'm
going to get deported.

01:23:27.940 --> 01:23:29.660
And I can't do that,
I have a child.

01:23:29.660 --> 01:23:30.560
And I want something.

01:23:30.560 --> 01:23:32.790
I wanted to do
something with my life.

01:23:32.790 --> 01:23:37.190
And then I got moved to the
foster care system, where I

01:23:37.190 --> 01:23:38.660
spent about two years in there.

01:23:38.660 --> 01:23:40.090
And I met this amazing work.

01:23:40.090 --> 01:23:41.930
And then I met my mentor.

01:23:41.930 --> 01:23:44.030
And everything started
being put together.

01:23:44.030 --> 01:23:46.100
I went to school,
got my GED, and then

01:23:46.100 --> 01:23:49.034
when I was going to
school, it's when

01:23:49.034 --> 01:23:50.450
I got to sit down
with people that

01:23:50.450 --> 01:23:53.630
had to spend decades of
their lives in prison

01:23:53.630 --> 01:23:55.460
and how much they suffer.

01:23:55.460 --> 01:23:57.710
And then I would ask them,
why you didn't do something

01:23:57.710 --> 01:23:58.209
about it.

01:23:58.209 --> 01:24:00.420
Look, but no-- they're
waiting for the other person.

01:24:00.420 --> 01:24:02.570
And then I decided
to be that person.

01:24:02.570 --> 01:24:07.580
And if there's one thing
that I have to go back to,

01:24:07.580 --> 01:24:08.690
I wouldn't change it.

01:24:08.690 --> 01:24:12.170
Even though I would love to
have been for my daughter

01:24:12.170 --> 01:24:12.810
all this time.

01:24:12.810 --> 01:24:16.470
But I am where I am because
of everything that I had done.

01:24:16.470 --> 01:24:18.120
And I'm liking myself.

01:24:18.120 --> 01:24:19.600
I'm starting to love myself.

01:24:19.600 --> 01:24:26.640
[APPLAUSE]

01:24:26.640 --> 01:24:29.220
SARAH ZARBA: Just listening
to you ladies, I mean,

01:24:29.220 --> 01:24:30.900
it's just echoing
the same thing.

01:24:30.900 --> 01:24:34.830
I was 14 the first time that I
was involved with the system.

01:24:34.830 --> 01:24:36.930
And I mean, I was in
the back of the police

01:24:36.930 --> 01:24:39.180
car, 14 years old,
handcuffed, because

01:24:39.180 --> 01:24:41.100
of a fight that
happened at home.

01:24:41.100 --> 01:24:44.860
And my parents, I mean,
they stayed together.

01:24:44.860 --> 01:24:46.500
They're still together today.

01:24:46.500 --> 01:24:51.570
And coming from Long Island,
which is a suburban community,

01:24:51.570 --> 01:24:54.540
that's not something
that is the norm there.

01:24:54.540 --> 01:24:57.060
So parents of limited resources
on what to [INAUDIBLE],

01:24:57.060 --> 01:24:59.400
like, what do you do when
your child is out of control?

01:24:59.400 --> 01:25:02.700
Or what do you do when your
kid is skipping school?

01:25:02.700 --> 01:25:04.680
And in that case,
the cops were called,

01:25:04.680 --> 01:25:06.330
and I was placed in handcuffs.

01:25:06.330 --> 01:25:09.150
And the whole ride, at 14, too.

01:25:09.150 --> 01:25:10.950
I didn't even know
where I was going.

01:25:10.950 --> 01:25:15.890
And I ended up getting
taken to the family court.

01:25:15.890 --> 01:25:17.520
And that there was
a petition filed,

01:25:17.520 --> 01:25:19.540
a PINS petition at the time.

01:25:19.540 --> 01:25:21.270
And it was just
so chaotic that I

01:25:21.270 --> 01:25:22.824
had no idea what was happening.

01:25:22.824 --> 01:25:24.990
I just thought, well, I
must have committed a crime.

01:25:24.990 --> 01:25:26.823
I must have done something
wrong because I'm

01:25:26.823 --> 01:25:28.050
in the back of this car.

01:25:28.050 --> 01:25:33.420
And that just continued on
from age 14 on until 18.

01:25:33.420 --> 01:25:35.820
And I just kept going
back and forth to court.

01:25:35.820 --> 01:25:39.810
Also in school, I was
considered homeless

01:25:39.810 --> 01:25:42.030
because I didn't live at home.

01:25:42.030 --> 01:25:46.710
And I was actually kicked out
of three different high schools.

01:25:46.710 --> 01:25:47.970
And it was very chaotic.

01:25:47.970 --> 01:25:50.100
And people in the
school district

01:25:50.100 --> 01:25:52.620
didn't understand
why I was acting out.

01:25:52.620 --> 01:25:54.125
I was disrupting class.

01:25:54.125 --> 01:25:57.420
I was disrupting everything
that came into my path,

01:25:57.420 --> 01:26:00.660
I just destroyed
it because I didn't

01:26:00.660 --> 01:26:02.010
have any support at home.

01:26:02.010 --> 01:26:04.890
And everything seemed that
it was fine from the outside,

01:26:04.890 --> 01:26:07.080
but no one was asking
those questions to find out

01:26:07.080 --> 01:26:08.670
what was really going on.

01:26:08.670 --> 01:26:10.650
And there was, at
the time, there

01:26:10.650 --> 01:26:13.590
is a probation officer stationed
in the school district.

01:26:13.590 --> 01:26:17.640
And she would-- full uniform,
school resource officer is what

01:26:17.640 --> 01:26:18.750
they're called now--

01:26:18.750 --> 01:26:21.150
and she would come to class,
make sure I was in class.

01:26:21.150 --> 01:26:24.300
And all my classmates
thought that I was a problem.

01:26:24.300 --> 01:26:26.850
No one wanted to
hang out with me.

01:26:26.850 --> 01:26:28.290
My friends, their
parents wouldn't

01:26:28.290 --> 01:26:32.190
allow them to hang out with me
because I was a problem child.

01:26:32.190 --> 01:26:35.490
So that continued,
and eventually I

01:26:35.490 --> 01:26:36.990
ended up in independent living.

01:26:36.990 --> 01:26:39.870
So when I turned 16, I was
eligible to go to this group

01:26:39.870 --> 01:26:41.550
home with other girls.

01:26:41.550 --> 01:26:44.460
And I started
experimenting with drugs.

01:26:44.460 --> 01:26:45.540
I was smoking weed.

01:26:45.540 --> 01:26:47.400
I mean I just wanted
some kind of escape,

01:26:47.400 --> 01:26:51.180
some kind of release, because
I didn't feel any connection

01:26:51.180 --> 01:26:54.804
to anyone, not even to myself.

01:26:54.804 --> 01:26:56.970
And then family court, going
back and forth to court

01:26:56.970 --> 01:26:59.330
during that time,
the legal aid who

01:26:59.330 --> 01:27:01.860
was supposed to be
representing me didn't ask me,

01:27:01.860 --> 01:27:02.607
what do you want?

01:27:02.607 --> 01:27:04.440
What's going on, or
what's going on at home?

01:27:04.440 --> 01:27:06.060
Or where do you want to go?

01:27:06.060 --> 01:27:08.560
So I just kind of cycled
through the system.

01:27:08.560 --> 01:27:12.960
And when I aged out at
18, there was no plan.

01:27:12.960 --> 01:27:14.980
There was no nowhere
for me to go.

01:27:14.980 --> 01:27:18.150
It was just like, well, you've
aged out of this system.

01:27:18.150 --> 01:27:21.780
And now we're just going to
leave you to your own devices.

01:27:21.780 --> 01:27:24.270
And what ended up
