01:43:15.790 --> 01:43:18.640
have boots on the
ground, it really

01:43:18.640 --> 01:43:23.110
inspires us on our team to
keep moving the company forward

01:43:23.110 --> 01:43:29.200
and challenging ourselves
to discuss this conversation

01:43:29.200 --> 01:43:31.450
and push where we
haven't pushed before.

01:43:31.450 --> 01:43:34.030
So our employees have
hosted movie screenings

01:43:34.030 --> 01:43:36.490
on mass incarceration,
both on campus

01:43:36.490 --> 01:43:39.370
and in the community; policy
convenings, like today,

01:43:39.370 --> 01:43:42.070
on criminal justice; brought
some of the nation's most

01:43:42.070 --> 01:43:44.570
prominent speakers and
voices in the movement,

01:43:44.570 --> 01:43:48.700
folks like Brian Stevenson and
Gina Clayton to our campus;

01:43:48.700 --> 01:43:52.480
and are volunteering in the
communities and in prisons.

01:43:52.480 --> 01:43:55.120
And we think that's
very important.

01:43:55.120 --> 01:43:59.380
